main event: A witness observed a bright, unusually outlined object in the sky over Panama City, Florida, on September 16, 1966.
interesting points: The object was brighter than a star and traveling in a northerly direction,The object was visible for about 5-10 seconds before being obscured by a building,The conclusion of the sighting was that the object could possibly be a satellite,The witness described the object as 'silver' and 'round' based on earlier sightings in May 1966,There were no photographs attached to the report despite mentions of objects observed.
sighted object: bright outlined object in the sky
witness description: A civilian observer who reported the sighting
